{
  "texts": [
    "Compared to 2017, the 2018 eht-imaging reconstructions without one antenna are affected by a stronger tessellation pattern.",
    "However, the morphology of the ring-like structure is more robust to the removal of a single site in 2018 compared to 2017.",
    "For example, in 2018, a ring-like structure is still distinguishable even without the Chile site.",
    "Also the removal of the LMT antenna does not affect the orientation of the ring, and the removal of PV does not strongly affect the morphology.",
    "A79, page 48 of 63 The Event Horizon Telescope Collaboration: A&A, 681, A79 (2024) Vis."
  ]
}